reviewText: As someone who has followed Bazan's career for quite a few years now, I was eagerly awaiting the release of this project and after watching it, I was not disappointed. The interviews are great, and musically, there's a little from the old stuff, the recent stuff, and even the new stuff. He lets us into his life a bit, and while it was obviously done on a modest budget, creatively speaking it's still pretty cool. Check it out, he is one of the most underrated songwriters of our time.
